The company had <a href="https://www.theblock.co/post/262100/usdc-stablecoin-issuer-circle-mulls-ipo-in-2024-bloomberg" data-v-f87c67ca="">previously</a> been talking to advisers about a potential IPO, Bloomberg reported in November, citing anonymous sources. "While it’s not clear how much Circle would seek to be valued in an IPO, it was valued at $9 billion when it tried to go public in a blank-check deal in 2022," the report said at the time.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
In 2021, Circle <a href="https://www.theblock.co/post/110806/confirmed-stablecoin-firm-circle-public-spac-merger" data-v-f87c67ca="">agreed to go public</a> through a merger with a Special Purpose Acquisition Company named Concord Acquisition Corp., but that arrangement later fizzled out.&nbsp;
